---
alwaysApply: true
---
Prioritize simplicity and avoid writing over explanatory comments. Docstrings
are good but don't add comments to highlight prompt requests. Do not write new
markdown files and avoid adding new sections to existing markdown files unless
explicitly asked to do it. When writing markdown, avoid adding comments to code
blocks. This is wrong:

```bash
# Mise automatically installs dependencies
mise run build

# Run the app
mise run run
```

Instead, write each command in a separate block and add the comment as text:

Mise automatically installs dependencies
```bash
mise run build
```

Run the app
```bash
mise run run
```
